==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Discrepancy
<hw>Dis*crep"an*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>-ances</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, <plw>-ancies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>disrepantia</ets>: cf. OF. <ets>discrepance</ets>. See <er>Discrepant</er>.]</ety> <def>The state or quality of being discrepant; disagreement; variance; discordance; dissimilarity; contrariety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There hath been ever a <qex>discrepance</qex> of vesture of youth and age, men and women.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T. Elyot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is no real <qex>discrepancy</qex> between these two genealogies.</q> <rj><qau>G. S. Faber.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discrepant</ent>⟦br⟧
